#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:3
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr "詞彙表"

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:6
msgid "General"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:13
msgid "LLVM backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:15
msgid ""
"A (*Clang*) compiler backend that converts the :term:`LLVM` Intermediate "
"Representation (IR) to code for a specified machine or other languages. In "
"the case of Emscripten, the specified target is JavaScript."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:28
msgid "Load-store consistency"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:30
msgid ""
"Load-Store Consistency (LSC), is the requirement that after a value with a "
"specific type is written to a memory location, loads from that memory "
"location will be of the same type. So if a variable contains a 32-bit "
"floating point number, then both loads and stores to that variable will be "
"of 32-bit floating point values, and not 16-bit unsigned integers or "
"anything else."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:32
msgid ""
"This definition is taken from `Emscripten: An LLVM-to-JavaScript Compiler "
"<https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/blob/main/docs/paper.pdf?"
"raw=true>`_ (section 2.1.1). There is additional detail in that paper."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:16
msgid "Minifying"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:18
msgid ""
"`Minification <http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minification_(programming)>`_ in "
"JavaScript is the process of removing all unnecessary characters from source "
"code without changing its functionality. At higher optimisation levels "
"Emscripten uses the :term:`Closure Compiler` to minify Emscripten code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:19
msgid "Relooping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:21
msgid ""
"Recreate high-level loop and ``if`` structures from the low-level labels and "
"branches that appear in LLVM assembly (definition taken from `this paper "
"<https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/blob/main/docs/paper.pdf?"
"raw=true>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:22
msgid "SDL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:24
msgid ""
"`Simple DirectMedia Layer <https://www.libsdl.org/>`_ (SDL) is a cross-"
"platform development library designed to provide low level access to audio, "
"keyboard, mouse, joystick, and graphics hardware via OpenGL and Direct3D."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:26
msgid ""
"The original compiler supported a number of other memory models and "
"compilation modes (see `Code Generation Modes <https://github.com/emscripten-"
"core/emscripten/wiki/Code-Generation-Modes>`_) but *Typed Arrays Mode 2* "
"proved to have, among other benefits, the greatest support for arbitrary "
"code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:10
msgid "XHR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:12
msgid ""
"Contraction of ``XMLHttpRequest``. Emscripten uses XHRs for asynchronously "
"downloading binary data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:36
msgid "Emscripten tools and dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:58
msgid "Binaryen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:60
msgid ""
"`Binaryen <https://github.com/WebAssembly/binaryen/>`_ is a WebAssembly "
"compiler toolkit, which Emscripten uses to modify and optimize Wasm."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:40
msgid "Clang"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:42
msgid ""
"Clang is a compiler front end for C, C++, and other programming languages "
"that uses :term:`LLVM` as its back end."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:75
msgid "Closure Compiler"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:77
msgid ""
"The closure compiler is used to minify Emscripten-generated code at higher "
"optimisations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:49
msgid "Compiler Configuration File"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:51
msgid ""
"The :ref:`Compiler Configuration File <compiler-configuration-file>` stores "
"the :term:`active <Active Tool/SDK>` tools and SDKs as defined using :term:"
"`emsdk activate <emsdk>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:43
msgid "emcc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:45
msgid ""
"The :ref:`emccdoc`. Emscripten's drop-in replacement for a compiler like "
"*gcc*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:46
msgid "Emscripten Command Prompt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:48
msgid ""
"The :ref:`emcmdprompt` is used to call Emscripten tools from the command "
"line on Windows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:55
msgid "Fastcomp"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:57
msgid ""
"Fastcomp was Emscripten's second compiler core, after the JS compiler and "
"before the new LLVM Wasm backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:78
msgid "Git"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:80
msgid ""
"`Git <http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git_(software)>`_ is a distributed "
"revision control system. Emscripten is hosted on :term:`GitHub` and can be "
"updated and modified using a git client."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:81
msgid "GitHub"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:83
msgid ""
"`GitHub <https://github.com/>`_ is a :term:`Git` repository web-based "
"hosting service that also offers project-based collaboration features "
"including wikis, task management, and bug tracking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:85
msgid "The Emscripten project is hosted on GitHub."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:67
msgid "Java"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:69
msgid ""
"`Java <http://www.java.com/en/download/faq/whatis_java.xml>`_ is a "
"programming language and computing platform. It is used by Emscripten for "
"the code that performs some advanced optimisations. The required version is "
"listed in the :ref:`toolchain requirements <central-list-of-emscripten-tools-"
"and-dependencies>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:70
msgid "JavaScript"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:72
msgid ""
"`JavaScript <http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JavaScript>`_ (`ECMAScript <http://"
"en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ECMAScript>`_) is a programming language that is "
"primarily used as part of a web browser, providing programmatic access to "
"objects within a host environment. With :term:`node.js`, it is also being "
"used in server-side network programming."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:74
msgid ""
"The `asm.js <http://asmjs.org/faq.html>`_ subset of JavaScript is "
"Emscripten's target output language."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:86
msgid "lli"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:87
msgid "LLVM Interpreter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:89
msgid ""
"The `LLVM interpreter (LLI) <http://llvm.org/releases/3.0/docs/CommandGuide/"
"html/lli.html>`_ executes programs from :term:`LLVM` bitcode. This tool is "
"not maintained and has odd errors and crashes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:52
msgid "LLVM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:54
msgid ""
"`LLVM <http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LLVM>`_ is a compiler infrastructure "
"designed to allow optimization of programs written in arbitrary programming "
"languages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:61
msgid "node.js"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:63
msgid ""
"`Node.js <https://nodejs.org/en/>`_ is a cross-platform runtime environment "
"for server-side and networking applications written in JavaScript. "
"Essentially it allows you to run JavaScript applications outside of a "
"browser context."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:64
msgid "Python"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:66
msgid ""
"Python is a scripting language used to write many of Emscripten's tools. The "
"required version is listed in the :ref:`toolchain requirements <central-list-"
"of-emscripten-tools-and-dependencies>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:93
msgid "SDK Terms"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:95
msgid ""
"The following terms are used when referring to the SDK and :ref:`emsdk`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:98
msgid "emsdk"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:100
msgid ""
"The :ref:`emsdk` is used to perform all SDK maintenance and can install, "
"update, add, remove and :term:`activate <Active Tool/SDK>` :term:`SDKs "
"<SDK>` and :term:`tools <Tool>`. Most operations are of the form ``./emsdk "
"command``. To access the *emsdk* script, launch the :term:`Emscripten "
"Command Prompt`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:101
msgid "Tool"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:103
msgid ""
"The basic unit of software bundled in the :term:`SDK`. A Tool has a name and "
"a version. For example, **clang-3.2-32bit** is a tool that contains the 32-"
"bit version of the *Clang* v3.2 compiler. Other tools used by *Emscripten* "
"include :term:`Java`, :term:`Git`, :term:`node.js`, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:104
msgid "SDK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:106
msgid ""
"A set of :term:`tools <Tool>`. For example, **sdk-1.5.6-32bit** is an SDK "
"consisting of the tools: clang-3.2-32bit, node-0.10.17-32bit, "
"python-2.7.5.1-32bit and emscripten-1.5.6."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:108
msgid ""
"There are a number of different Emscripten SDK packages. These can be "
"downloaded from :ref:`here <sdk-download-and-install>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:109
msgid "Active Tool/SDK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:111
msgid ""
"The :term:`emsdk` can store multiple versions of :term:`tools <Tool>` and :"
"term:`SDKs <SDK>`. The active tools/SDK is the set of tools that are used by "
"default on the *Emscripten Command Prompt*. This compiler configuration is "
"stored in an emsdk-specific config file (**.emscripten**) and can be changed "
"using *emsdk*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:116
msgid "emsdk root directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:118
msgid ""
"The :term:`emsdk` can manage any number of :term:`tools <Tool>` and :term:"
"`SDKs <SDK>`, and these are stored in :term:`subdirectories <SDK root "
"directory>` of the *emsdk root directory*. The **emsdk root** is the "
"directory specified when you first installed an SDK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:119
msgid "SDK root directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:121
msgid ""
"The :term:`emsdk` can store any number of tools and SDKs. The *SDK root "
"directory* is the directory used to store a particular :term:`SDK`. It is "
"located as follows, with respect to the :term:`emsdk root directory`: "
"**<emsdk root>\\\\emscripten\\\\<sdk root directory>\\\\**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:125
msgid "Site / Sphinx"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:129
msgid "reStructured text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/site/glossary.rst:131
msgid ""
"Markup language used to define content on this site. See the `reStructured "
"text primer <http://sphinx-doc.org/rest.html>`_."
msgstr ""
